The paper discusses privacy-preserving techniques for mobile sensor data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed feature learning architecture also involves machine learning techniques for transforming raw sensor data, which is a common topic in the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset for activity and attribute recognition, which falls under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and computer vision (cs.CY).
